# AI Kit

On first interaction with a new task, read `AGENTS.md` in the project root.
If present, read `rules/app-context.mdc` for a minimal app snapshot.
After hydration, run `/hydrate-verify`.
For doc markers, dissent protocol, and anti-patterns, follow `AGENTS.md`.

## Commands

Use native Cursor commands (type `/` in chat) for common workflows:

- `/plan` - Architectural blueprint before coding
- `/build` - Production-ready implementation
- `/verify` - Code review and safety check
- `/hydrate-verify` - Hydration verification
- `/fix` - Quick targeted correction
- `/debug` - Root cause analysis
- `/refactor` - Improve code quality
- `/commit` - Create git commit
- `/discuss` - Technical debate
- `/explain` - Code walkthrough
